message.content:
cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.DB, cs.PL, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with formal modeling and verification of safety properties using an array-based backward reachability procedure.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper proposes an extension of BPMN for data-aware processes and discusses verification of safety properties.
- cs.DB (Databases) is relevant as the paper deals with partitioning data into a read-only catalog and a read-write repository.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper proposes an extension of BPMN and discusses verification of safety properties using an SMT model checker.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper discusses verification of safety properties using techniques inspired by the literature on verification of artifact systems.
